By Week 35, the story is less about a single shock than about density. The week of September 13\'9619, 2025, reads as a time when many lines that once separated power from impulse were thinned at once. Immigration, policing, science, media, and money all moved a little closer to the president\'92s hand. Yet the Democracy Clock did not advance. It stayed at 7:58 p.m., not because the week was safe, but because the dangers it revealed were already built into the hour. What changed was not the time, but how clearly we could see what that time meant.\
