That same logic extended to Memphis and Louisiana. In Memphis, Trump signed an order creating the \'93Memphis Safe Task Force,\'94 embedding National Guard units alongside FBI, ATF, DEA, ICE, Marshals, and Justice Department personnel in city policing. Tennessee\'92s governor welcomed the deployment, but local officials warned of militarization in a city with historically low crime. In Louisiana, the administration drafted a plan to send a thousand Guard troops into New Orleans and Baton Rouge for law enforcement duties, contingent on a friendly governor\'92s request. These moves did not respond to hurricanes or riots. They treated routine urban crime and political disagreement as grounds for federalized force. The effect was structural. It normalized a presidency that can reach for troops whenever a city is Democratic\uc0\u8209 run, resistant on immigration, or simply useful as a stage.\
